hopobject.body: Thanks for calling cost of aids drugs in africa And Don is coming dangerously close to losing his. He has been juggling his mistress, his second wife and his family for some time now (something suggested by Roger's orange-juggling trick at the beginning of the episode). But once Sally walked in on him and Sylvia, that all came crashing down. While everyone else thinks Don is a saint for what he did for the Rosens, Sally knows he is a sinner. Will the scorn of his daughter be enough for Don to change his ways? Judging by the way he was able to walk away from Sally's door once he knew she would not blow his cover, not likely.
